1. Set Locale to Support UTF-8

locale  # Check current locale
sudo apt update && sudo apt install locales
sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8
sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8

2. Add ROS 2 Apt Repository

sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository universe
sudo apt update
sudo apt install curl -y
sudo curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.key -o /usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg] http://packages.ros.org/ros2/ubuntu noble main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros2.list > /dev/null

3. Update Package Lists

sudo apt update

4. Install ROS 2
For most users, the Desktop version is recommended:
sudo apt install ros-jazzy-desktop

(sudo apt install ros-rolling-ros-base for base version)

5. Install Additional Tools (Optional)

sudo apt install python3-colcon-common-extensions python3-rosdep python3-vcstool
Initialize rosdep

6. Set up rosdep to manage dependencies:

sudo rosdep init
rosdep update
Source ROS 2 Environment

6.1 Add ROS 2 to your shell to access commands:

source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash

6.2 To make this permanent, add it to your ~/.bashrc:

echo "source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc

7. Verify Installation

7.1 Start terminal
source /opt/ros/jazzy/setup.bash
ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp talker

7.2 In another terminal, you should see the talker publishing messages and the listener receiving them.
source /opt/ros/jazzy/setup.bash
ros2 run demo_nodes_py listener
